      • isEligible

        public static void isEligible(DataEx.EligibleListener callback)

        Determines if the device is eligible to opt into DataEx.

        Parameters:
        callback - Instance of the interface DataEx.EligibleListener class for DataEx to respond with. Callbacks will be fired on the UI thread.

      • showTakeover

        public static void showTakeover(android.content.Context context)

        Show the DataEx optin Takeover activity. The activity will be started with Activity.startActivityForResult with a request code of REQUEST_TAKEOVER_STATUS. If you wish to act on the user completing onboarding (such as for analytic purposes), you can override Activity.onActivityResult and capture the result for REQUEST_TAKEOVER_STATUS.

        Parameters:
        context - Context to start activity with. This should be an activity context.
        See Also:
        Activity.startActivityForResult, Activity.onActivityResult

      • takeoverInstance

        public static java.lang.Class<? extends androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity> takeoverInstance()

        If you have the need to launch our optin activity in a special way, this will return the appropriate class to be used when constructing your intent.

        Returns:
        instance of the class TakeoverActivity class

      • isWalletInstalled

      • init

        public static DataEx init(android.content.Context context)

        Initialize DataEx. This will automatically be done for you in most situations, but if you need to change the server environment that DataEx uses you can call this directly with the appropriate environment.

        Parameters:
        context - a reference to the application context. If a non application context is provided, DataEx will grab the application context from it. * @param environment Which server environment DataEx should use. By default this is Environment.Dev
